Jupyter
- freely available web application
- enables creation and sharing of document containing equations, live coding,
  visualizations, and narrative text
- provides an interacting computing environment that supports multiple programming
  languages, including Python, R, Julia and more
- shines brightest when used with Python
- revolves around notebooks, documents containing a mix of code, visualizations,
  narrative text, equations and multimedia content
- these notebooks allow users to create, share, and collaborate on computational
  projects seamlessly

Why Jupyter?
- flexibility and easy of use
- intuitive platform for writing, testing, and sharing code
- interactive interface enables data exploration, algorithm experimentation
  and result visualization all seamlessly integrated within a unified environment

Key Features of Jupyter
- Interactive Computing
- Support for Mutliple Languages
- Rich Output
- Integrations with Data Science Libraries

Jupyter in Data Science
- indispensable tool for researchers, analusts and developrs
- seamless integration with popular libraries (NumPy, pandas, sci-kit-learn)
  makes it the go-to choise for data manipulation, analysis, and machine learning
- user-friendly interface, interactive capablities, and robust collaboration features
- essential tool for anyone involved in data analysis, scientific research, education
  or software development
- empowers you to work for efficiently and share your insights with other
